metadata.name: GEN XYZ Das Occult #2651
metadata.description:
A 10k Generative Profile Pic collection
GEN XYZ Das Occult - by culla - @tamccullough

move over cryptopunks
there is a new group on the scene

100% code - not an image composition

A bunch of common palettes
A selection of rare palettes
And a smaller set of ultra rare palettes
However, rarity will be based on what combinations the code produces

The majority of tokens will not have a special trait
However your token might have one or even multiple special traits
But, be aware that only the last special trait added will be listed in the features

Even then, look closely, because not all aspects of the canvas are included in the features. Collectors should still look closely and choose what they like when buying on secondary.

Which team are you on? X or O?

follow culla on twitter for updates. Or maybe __acolyte__

If the non reserved tokens mint out quickly, Access List mints will have 24 hours to mint reserves assigned to those wallets

Thank you for supporting an emerging artist in the generative art space

Access List reserves were given to holders of the following PFP collections created by culla
2x for each Basqunk held
1x for each Inkspunk, TwoFourQunk, V0iD, DeeManz, Punkasso and CR0$$KULL
You would have needed to transfer the above tokens to your mint wallet at the time of the snapshot

share your tokens on social media with #genxyznft
Made with love by culla using p5.js

metadata.name: Rug of imagination #143
metadata.description:
I recently faced covid, I can say it was one of the worst moments of my life, I questioned my sanity and if I would stay alive. What comforted me was to remember my childhood, my past, and I remembered the rugs I used to sit on to play or listen to stories, it is amazing how in the day to day we forget the little things in life that make us happy, sometimes we stop living to just survive.

Artwork made with p5.js and p5.scribbles

metadata.name: sketch: cairn() #22
metadata.description:
A cairn is a monument made of stacked rocks. In modern times, often used for wayfinding in remote areas, as in mountaineering, or to indicate an area of significance.

In this sketch I imagine these monuments -- through the looking glass. Paying mind to the simplicity of their construction, as well as the mysticism of what each might represent.

---

Sketch is a series meant to celebrate learning and experimentation.

In this sketch I experiment with subdivision, smoothing, textures, multiple levels of domain warping, and illustration techniques.

---
- Made with p5js
- Press s to save png
- Use param ?width=x to render at size

metadata.name: Ghost Friend #109
metadata.description:
Everyone dreams of a friend that would never leave them (we prefer to call it "haunting" around here), that could follow you around no matter where you go (even if it involves going through brick walls) while also being able to scare away their toughest enemies - and trust me, there's no better option than a ghost friend!

Each ghost is created exclusively with code (mostly in p5.js) without any assets and has a unique yet universally charming appearance 👻

Credit for visual inspiration goes to spooky project by watabo_shi, as well as ghostly artworks by Jordan Jenkins, Jonas Mosesson, Rytis, amy luo, Marvin Rudolph and others.

License: CC-BY-SA 4.0

metadata.name: Effluence #271
metadata.description:
“Through our eyes, the universe is perceiving itself. Through our ears, the universe is listening to its harmonies. We are the witnesses through which the universe becomes conscious of its glory, of its magnificence.”

-Alan Wilson Watts


---

Depending on the feature values, this artwork may take several seconds to render.
A modern, capable computer is advised.

To download image at different resolutions, press keys:

1. Low
2. Mid
3. High

---

10 first people minting at auction start price can request high-quality print at no additional cost (DM on Twitter for more details if interested)

Made with p5.js, curiosity and goodwill.

---

Daniel Aguilar
October 2022

Twitter: @protozoo
Instagram: @prtzart
Website: https://protozoo.xyz

metadata.name: Hábitat #43
metadata.description:
"A subtle structure weaves form.
 A language winds life.
 A creation inhabits the Void."

I am deeply interested in the relationship between the tangible and the intangible.
Everything we see is sustained by a structure that is hidden, yet we can sense it.
That sensation creates Life.

This is my first generative art project published. Created using p5.
Press "s" to save a PNG image.
